  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Green-growth income initiatives for forest people</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will conduct research to inform a proposed new initiative around Metemma forest in Ethiopia. The objective of the initiative will be to increase incomes, stabilize livelihoods and generate employment for the poorest rural and forest-dependent communities in this area. Based on the success of previous community-based forest management projects, the initiative will also promote and professionalise the production, processing and selling of non-timber forest products, such as gum, resin and incense. This will ultimately lead to better conservation of the forest whilst reducing local poverty.</narrative>
  </description>
